WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.540 --> 00:00:01.540
Hello.

2
00:00:02.360 --> 00:00:06.500
To install CaseTrace, go to
casetrace.dk. Press download.

3
00:00:07.850 --> 00:00:08.890
It downloads the program.

4
00:00:09.240 --> 00:00:10.720
I have already downloaded it.

5
00:00:11.610 --> 00:00:13.336
Then you install in
the language you want.

6
00:00:13.360 --> 00:00:14.180
Press next.

7
00:00:14.350 --> 00:00:15.350
Install it.

8
00:00:15.610 --> 00:00:17.530
I'm canceling here
because I already have it.

9
00:00:18.080 --> 00:00:19.960
Then you open the program CaseTrace.

10
00:00:20.700 --> 00:00:22.100
Then I will show how it works.

11
00:00:22.890 --> 00:00:26.000
There are activities that log
everything you do on your computer.

12
00:00:26.950 --> 00:00:28.680
Then you have Folder time,
which is probably the interesting part.

13
00:00:29.920 --> 00:00:32.060
Here you can go in and add a folder.

14
00:00:32.180 --> 00:00:33.180
I add Show.

15
00:00:34.990 --> 00:00:39.100
So when I have added Show, I
can, for example, give it a budget.

16
00:00:40.520 --> 00:00:42.920
I can call that case number 1.

17
00:00:43.590 --> 00:00:47.040
And then say there are 10 hours
and an hourly rate of 750.

18
00:00:48.540 --> 00:00:52.100
Now this entire folder has
a budget of 7500 kroner.

19
00:00:52.990 --> 00:00:53.990
And we have 10 hours.

20
00:00:54.980 --> 00:00:56.260
Then I will try to open the folder.

21
00:00:57.200 --> 00:00:58.200
In here in the folder.

22
00:00:58.680 --> 00:00:59.680
I have two folders there.

23
00:00:59.900 --> 00:01:00.900
This one is empty.

24
00:01:02.140 --> 00:01:03.200
There is a file here.

25
00:01:04.120 --> 00:01:04.980
A text file.

26
00:01:05.140 --> 00:01:06.440
We are trying to open the text file.

27
00:01:07.660 --> 00:01:09.520
It's just to test.

28
00:01:10.480 --> 00:01:11.600
As soon as I open it.

29
00:01:12.120 --> 00:01:14.220
Then you can see the
program here starts to log.

30
00:01:15.390 --> 00:01:17.120
It's open right now and
it's counting seconds.

31
00:01:18.590 --> 00:01:23.380
When it counts up enough, it shows
how much money you have spent

32
00:01:23.530 --> 00:01:25.500
out of the 7500 and how much time
you have spent out of the 10 hours.

33
00:01:26.590 --> 00:01:28.080
And it also gives you notifications.

34
00:01:32.120 --> 00:01:35.680
I have already made two folders here.

35
00:01:36.430 --> 00:01:37.240
As I have added below.

36
00:01:37.320 --> 00:01:38.320
You can remove them again.

37
00:01:39.110 --> 00:01:40.150
There is one called test.

38
00:01:41.640 --> 00:01:44.120
Where I have some different
folders with subfolders.

39
00:01:44.450 --> 00:01:47.440
It even finds the subfolders
every time you open a document.

40
00:01:49.170 --> 00:01:51.880
Here you can see that
I only have number 10.

41
00:01:52.080 --> 00:01:52.920
Case X.

42
00:01:53.080 --> 00:01:54.360
And there I have used 19%.

43
00:01:57.620 --> 00:01:58.700
And here is a folder with 19%.

44
00:01:59.135 --> 00:02:05.000
So you can also put a budget on
the subfolders if that's what you want.

45
00:02:07.120 --> 00:02:11.860
In addition, we still have a program that
logs all files you open on your computer.

46
00:02:12.440 --> 00:02:14.580
How many times each file has been opened.

47
00:02:14.700 --> 00:02:16.000
And for what period of time.

48
00:02:17.080 --> 00:02:18.580
And you can go in and see the dashboard.

49
00:02:18.960 --> 00:02:21.120
How many hours you spent in your day.

50
00:02:22.140 --> 00:02:23.460
Then you can go into settings.

51
00:02:24.580 --> 00:02:25.620
Sorry, help.

52
00:02:26.120 --> 00:02:28.620
In here you can make a database backup.

53
00:02:30.210 --> 00:02:32.760
You can see when it
needs to make a backup.

54
00:02:34.090 --> 00:02:35.610
In which days or hours and minutes.

55
00:02:35.650 --> 00:02:36.970
How many backups there should be.

56
00:02:37.490 --> 00:02:39.406
And then they are down here
so you always have a backup.

57
00:02:39.430 --> 00:02:42.100
You can store the backup
on OneDrive if you want.

58
00:02:42.955 --> 00:02:44.115
Or locally on your computer.

59
00:02:45.620 --> 00:02:46.740
Last but not least.

60
00:02:46.815 --> 00:02:49.460
Then we have billable hours per day.

61
00:02:49.680 --> 00:02:50.600
Here we can go in.

62
00:02:50.660 --> 00:02:51.960
So we'll just start today.

63
00:02:52.710 --> 00:02:53.870
Then we can print here as a PDF.

64
00:02:55.820 --> 00:02:56.920
Then it pops up here.

65
00:02:59.710 --> 00:03:01.630
Then we can see that these are
the hours we saw inside Folder time.

66
00:03:02.270 --> 00:03:03.680
Here are the hours used.

67
00:03:05.800 --> 00:03:07.220
They are then inside the document.
